From: SRB2Kart PS Vita port
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] glTexImage2D: do not upload with a NULL write callback

When `internalFormat` is not one of the supported enums, the switch sets
`error = GL_INVALID_ENUM` and *breaks* -- but execution continues and
`gpu_alloc_texture()` is still called with `write_cb == NULL`. It then does
`write_cb(dst, clr)` in its pixel loop: a branch to address 0, i.e. a prefetch
abort that kills the app with no diagnostic.

This is easy to hit from a real engine: SRB2's `textureformatGL` is 0 until the
GL context is fully set up, and any code path that uploads a texture before that
crashes instead of returning GL_INVALID_ENUM.

Return instead of falling through.

---
--- a/source/textures.c
+++ b/source/textures.c
@@ -197,9 +197,9 @@
 			tex_format = SCE_GXM_TEXTURE_FORMAT_P8_ABGR;
 			break;
 		default:
 			error = GL_INVALID_ENUM;
-			break;
+			return;
 		}
 
 		// Checking if texture is too big for sceGxm
 		if (width > GXM_TEX_MAX_SIZE || height > GXM_TEX_MAX_SIZE) {
